          "text": "Overview",
          "type": "heading"
        },
        {
          "type": "paragraph",
          "inlineContent": [
            {
              "type": "text",
              "text": "Responder objects can implement the methods of this protocol to handle standard editing-related actions. For example, a "
            },
            {
              "type": "reference",
              "isActive": true,
              "identifier": "doc://com.apple.documentation/documentation/uikit/uimenucontroller"
            },
            {
              "type": "text",
              "text": " object reports editing actions using these methods. The menu controller then asks UIKit to search the responder chain for an object that implements the appropriate method, calling the method on the first object that implements it. "
            }
          ]
        }
      ]
    }
